Are you curious what Remote Learning looks like at Farmersville ISD? Well, we have your answers. After much thoughtful planning, we put together our Remote Learning Overview. Follow this link http://www.farmersvilleisd.net/remotelearning/ to our website where you can read the overview.

Then tomorrow morning we invite you to return to our Farmersville ISD Facebook page or our website(www.farmersvilleisd.net) to fill out our Education Commitment Form for your student(s). This is how we will be able to start determining our class sizes. Thank you for your patience and understanding during this crazy time in our world. We are determined to have this be another great year for our Farmersville Farmers! #GoFarmers

Join us on the High School Football Field for this informative parent meeting at 7:30pm on July 28!

Topics:
- Football Season
- Handbooks
- Paperwork
- Schedules-Practice
- Game/Expectations

Notes:
We need one parent for High School football athletes or trainers to be in attendance on 7/28/20 to discuss the upcoming football season.

Please wear a mask and social distancing guidelines will be followed. If you have any questions please email Coach Hankins bhankins@farmersvilleisd.org.

Please do not attend if you are not feeling well and have symptoms of covid, or you have been exposed to anyone with covid. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation. See you on July 28!

Farmersville ISD is committed to providing an exceptional education for every student regardless of the barriers that COVID-19 has created. To that end, we are asking that each family complete the survey linked below. This information will help the District formulate a learning model whether in-person or virtually that will meet the needs of our families and comply with the guidelines of the state. No one knows what the upcoming school year will look like, but FISD will ensure that ALL students receive quality instruction. Please be reassured that FISD puts every student's health, well-being, and academic readiness as our highest priorities.

Survey Link:
https://bit.ly/fisdparentsurvey

Thank you in advance!

Farmersville ISD Administration

post_text:
Farmersville Athletes: Summer workouts will resume June 8th. UIL has released plans and protocols for schools to use. We as a staff will put plans together for summer workouts and sports specific training next week. We will have an organized and well thought out plan. All plans will be sent out via text/Remind/twitter/Farmersville ISD website/Facebook. Please check proper channels on Wednesday at 12:00pm. Our plan will safe and efficient in order for our athletes to have the best opportunity available for lifting/conditioning and sports specific training. Summer workouts will be for all incoming 7th-12th grade male/female athletes or athletes who plan on being in athletics. There will more than likely be numerous sessions to accommodate athletes and stay within the guidelines set by UIL. Thank you for being patient and flexible. We look forward to seeing each of you over the summer. #VISION20 #FARMERPRIDE

Coach Hankins

They also need to clean out their athletic locker at that time. On Monday April 27th go to the parking lot where the HS weight room door is. post_text:
Farmersville ISD Child Nutrition will be handing out meals beginning Tuesday 3/17/2020. Meals will be available at Tatum Elementary campus bus lane, by the covered awnings. (405 North Washington Street, Farmersville, TX)
Breakfast sacks will be handed out 7:30 to 8:30.
Lunch sacks will be handed out 11:30 to 12:30.
Meals will be provided to any child 1 year old to 18 years old.
Children are not required to be enrolled at Farmerville ISD and children do not need to be approved for any school meals program to receive these free sack meals. Texas Department of Agriculture requires children to be present to receive a meal, but they will not be required to enter the building.
We look forward to serving breakfast and lunch ‚Äúgrab and go‚Äù meals to kids at Tatum campus bus lane location starting 3/17/20 through 3/20/20. As circumstance change concerning meal availability, we will update our website.

post_text: Farmersville High School is postponing indefinitely the 2020 Junior-Senior Prom due to the Coronavirus pandemic and health crisis. With FISD being closed for an extended Spring Break in response to this health situation, the FHS administration is taking this action to protect the safety and well-being of our students and staff. Due to the rapidly changing nature of this health crisis, no tentative date for the 2020 prom has been set at this time.
text: Farmersville High School is postponing indefinitely the 2020 Junior-Senior Prom due to the Coronavirus pandemic and health crisis. With FISD being closed for an extended Spring Break in response to this health situation, the FHS administration is taking this action to protect the safety and well-being of our students and staff. Due to the rapidly changing nature of this health crisis, no tentative date for the 2020 prom has been set at this time.

post_text:
With the rapidly changing environment impacted by the declared Covid-19 pandemic, Farmersville ISD will extend Spring Break by one week. At this time, we expect school to resume on March 23, 2020. In an abundance of caution, we will close all activities until further notice. The circumstances are unprecedented and we will work to solve issues in the best interest of FISD students, staff and the public. We are in contact with health officials in Collin County and with the Texas Education Agency. Please plan accordingly for your family and their safety. We don't know what the future holds, but extended breaks with instruction offered online is a possibility. We will update our website and Facebook pages as information becomes available. Thank you for your patience and understanding in these difficult times. Please practice preventative measures and social distancing.

Sincerely,
Jeff Adams

post_text:
Dear Farmersville High School Community,

Tuesday, it was reported that one of our students made a statement that was perceived as a threat toward some of our students. During the investigation, it was concluded that the statements qualified as a threat and the student was removed from campus.

It is always the district emergency protocol to address school safety concerns and enlist the support of our school Police Department. We are fortunate that our school police department is here to support and investigate such issues.

An important reminder to all parents and guardians, please tell your children to report any frightening situations or concerns. If you see something say something. By the same token, please tell your children to refrain from joking about acts of violence and terror. Please note that making such statements can be construed as threats and may result in prosecution.

It also a good idea to monitor social media and Facebook accounts to know firsthand your children‚Äôs activities and clear up any possible misconceptions that maybe posted regarding violent behavior.
text:
Dear Farmersville High School Community,

Tuesday, it was reported that one of our students made a statement that was perceived as a threat toward some of our students. During the investigation, it was concluded that the statements qualified as a threat and the student was removed from campus.

It is always the district emergency protocol to address school safety concerns and enlist the support of our school Police Department. We are fortunate that our school police department is here to support and investigate such issues.

An important reminder to all parents and guardians, please tell your children to report any frightening situations or concerns. If you see something say something. By the same token, please tell your children to refrain from joking about acts of violence and terror. Please note that making such statements can be construed as threats and may result in prosecution.

It also a good idea to monitor social media and Facebook accounts to know firsthand your children‚Äôs activities and clear up any possible misconceptions that maybe posted regarding violent behavior.

By the same token, please tell your children to refrain from joking about acts of violence and terror. Please note that making such statements may be construed as threats and may result in prosecution.

It also a good idea to monitor social media and Facebook accounts to know firsthand your children‚Äôs activities and clear up any possible misconceptions that maybe posted regarding violent behavior.

post_text: Congratulations to the students and staff of Farmersville High School for achieving distinctions in all seven areas of the Texas Education Agency 2017 Accountability Summary. FHS earned distinctions in ELA/Reading, Mathematics, Science, Social Studies, Top 25% Student Progress, Top 25% Closing Performance Gaps, and Postsecondary Readiness. Farmersville High School and Farmersville Junior High were two of only 467 schools in the state (out of over 8,700 campuses) to achieve this distinction this year. Way to go Farmers!

post_text: Despite tonight's 26-42 loss to Pottsboro in the regional semifinals, the FHS faculty and Farmer fans are very proud of our Fightin' Farmers. Our Farmers finished the season with an 11-2 season record and won both the bi-district and area championships. Great job Coach Burnett and the Farmers!
text: Despite tonight's 26-42 loss to Pottsboro in the regional semifinals, the FHS faculty and Farmer fans are very proud of our Fightin' Farmers. Our Farmers finished the season with an 11-2 season record and won both the bi-district and area championships. Great job Coach Burnett and the Farmers!

post_text: Join us on Saturday at 4 pm in front of the high school as the band and cheerleaders lead a send-off to wish our Fightin' Farmers good luck before heading out to Allen Eagles Stadium. The Farmers will take on Pottsboro Saturday at 7:30 pm in the regional semi-finals.

post_text:
November 7, 2016

F.I.S.D has an ongoing investigation from graffiti found on a stool at FHS. At this time no credible threat has been found. F.I.S.D will continue to monitor the situation, plus have a strong security presence. All threats to our school and students are taken seriously and investigated thoroughly.

F.I.S.D makes security a top priority each and every day.

Thank you for your cooperation.



Sincerely,

Jeff Adams
Superintendent of Farmersville ISD
